trapDeviceMgmtUrl.name: trapDeviceMgmtUrl

trapDeviceDetails.name: trapDeviceDetails
trapDeviceDetails.description: A string details information about the device, including model, serial number, part number, etc....

trapDeviceName.description: A string contains the name of the device.

trapCritical.description: A critical alarm has occurred. Action: Check the Trap Details for more information.

trapWarning.name: trapWarning
trapWarning.description: A warning alarm has occurred. Action: Check the Trap Details for more information.

trapInformation.name: trapInformation

trapCleared.name: trapCleared

pduFirmwareVersion.description: The firmware revision level of the device.

pduStatus.name: pduStatus
pduStatus.description: The overall status of the device. A value of OK(2) indicates the device is operating normally. A value of degraded(3) indicates the device is operating with warning indicators. A value of failed(4) indicates the device is operating with critical indicators.

pduControllable.name: pduControllable
pduControllable.description: This object indicates whether or not the device is controllable.

pduInputTable.name: pduInputTable
pduInputTable.description: The Aggregate Object with number of entries equal to NumOfPdu and including the PduInput group.

pduInputEntry.name: pduInputEntry
pduInputEntry.description: The input table entry containing the voltage and current for the PDU

inputVoltage.name: inputVoltage
inputVoltage.description: The measured input voltage from the PDU meters in volts.

inputCurrent.name: inputCurrent
inputCurrent.description: The measured input current from the PDU meters in amps.

pduOutputTable.name: pduOutputTable
pduOutputTable.description: The Aggregate Object with number of entries equal to NumOfPdu and including the PduInput group.

pduOutputEntry.name: pduOutputEntry
pduOutputEntry.description: The input table entry containing the name, heat load, current load, power load, firmware, etc.

pduOutputLoad.name: pduOutputLoad
pduOutputLoad.description: The device output load in percent of rated capacity. A value of -1 will be returned if the heat load is unable to be measured.

pduOutputHeat.name: pduOutputHeat
pduOutputHeat.description: The total heat load measured on the PDU in BTUs. A value of -1 will be returned if the heat load is unable to be measured.

pduOutputPower.name: pduOutputPower
pduOutputPower.description: The total power load measured on the PDU in watts. A value of -1 will be returned if the power load is unable to be measured.

pduOutputNumBreakers.name: pduOutputNumBreakers
pduOutputNumBreakers.description: The number of breakers for the device. This variable indicates the number of rows in the breakers table.

pduOutputBreakerTable.name: pduOutputBreakerTable
pduOutputBreakerTable.description: List of breaker table entries. The number of entries is given by pduOutputNumBreakers .

pduOutputBreakerEntry.name: pduOutputBreakerEntry
pduOutputBreakerEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to an breaker.

breakerCurrent.name: breakerCurrent
breakerCurrent.description: The breaker current draw in Amps.

breakerStatus.name: breakerStatus
breakerStatus.description: This object indicates the status of the breaker. A value of normal(1) indicates the breaker is operating normally. A value of overloadWarning(2) indicates the breaker has an overload warning. A value of overloadCritical(3) indicates the breaker is overloaded. A value of voltageRangeWarning(4) indicates the breaker voltage is out of tolerance by 10-20%. A value of voltageRangeCritical(5) indicates the breaker voltage is out of tolerance by more than 20%. Note: Overload status has priority over voltage tolerance status.

upsIdentModel.name: upsIdentModel
upsIdentModel.description: The UPS Model;Part number;Serial number (e.g. HP R5500 XR;204451-B21;B00123456W).

upsIdentSoftwareVersions.name: upsIdentSoftwareVersions
upsIdentSoftwareVersions.description: The firmware revision level(s) of the UPS microcontroller(s).

upsIdentOemCode.name: upsIdentOemCode
upsIdentOemCode.description: A binary code indicating vendor. This should be a ?0x0c? for HP

upsBatTimeRemaining.name: upsBatTimeRemaining
upsBatTimeRemaining.description: Battery run time in seconds before UPS turns off due to low battery.

upsBatVoltage.name: upsBatVoltage
upsBatVoltage.description: Battery voltage as reported by the UPS meters.

upsBatCurrent.name: upsBatCurrent
upsBatCurrent.description: Battery Current as reported by the UPS metering. Current is positive when discharging, negative when recharging the battery.

upsBatteryAbmStatus.name: upsBatteryAbmStatus
upsBatteryAbmStatus.description: Gives the status of the Advanced Battery Management; batteryFloating(3) status means that the charger is temporarily charging the battery to its float voltage; batteryResting(4) is the state when the battery is fully charged and none of the other actions (charging/discharging/floating) is being done.

upsInputFrequency.name: upsInputFrequency
upsInputFrequency.description: The utility line frequency in tenths of Hz.

upsInputLineBads.name: upsInputLineBads
upsInputLineBads.description: The number of times the Input was out of tolerance in voltage or frequency.

upsInputTable.description: The Aggregate Object with number of entries equal to NumPhases and including the UpsInput group.

upsInputEntry.description: The input table entry containing the current, voltage, etc.

upsInputVoltage.description: The measured input voltage from the UPS meters in volts.

upsInputCurrent.name: upsInputCurrent
upsInputCurrent.description: The measured input current from the UPS meters in amps.

upsInputWatts.name: upsInputWatts
upsInputWatts.description: The measured input real power in watts.

upsInputSource.name: upsInputSource
upsInputSource.description: The present external source of input power. The enumeration none(2) indicates that there is no external source of power, for example, the UPS is On Battery (an internal source). The bypassFeed(4) can only be used when the Bypass source is known to be a separate utility feed than the primaryUtility(3).

upsOutputLoad.name: upsOutputLoad
upsOutputLoad.description: The UPS output load in percent of rated capacity.

upsOutputFrequency.name: upsOutputFrequency
upsOutputFrequency.description: The measured UPS output frequency in tenths of Hz.

upsOutputNumPhases.name: upsOutputNumPhases
upsOutputNumPhases.description: The number of metered output phases, serves as the table index.

upsOutputTable.description: The Aggregate Object with number of entries equal to NumPhases and including the UpsOutput group.

upsOutputEntry.description: Output Table Entry containing voltage, current, etc.

upsOutputPhase.name: upsOutputPhase
upsOutputPhase.description: The number {1..3} of the output phase.

upsOutputVoltage.name: upsOutputVoltage
upsOutputVoltage.description: The measured output voltage from the UPS metering in volts.

upsOutputCurrent.name: upsOutputCurrent
upsOutputCurrent.description: The measured UPS output current in amps.

upsOutputWatts.name: upsOutputWatts
upsOutputWatts.description: The measured real output power in watts.

upsOutputSource.name: upsOutputSource
upsOutputSource.description: The present source of output power. The enumeration none(2) indicates that there is no source of output power (and therefore no output power), for example, the system has opened the output breaker.

upsBypassFrequency.name: upsBypassFrequency
upsBypassFrequency.description: The bypass frequency in tenths of Hz.

upsBypassNumPhases.name: upsBypassNumPhases
upsBypassNumPhases.description: The number of lines in the UPS bypass table.

upsBypassPhase.name: upsBypassPhase
upsBypassPhase.description: The Bypass Phase, index for the table.

upsBypassVoltage.name: upsBypassVoltage
upsBypassVoltage.description: The measured UPS bypass voltage in volts.

upsEnvAmbientTemp.name: upsEnvAmbientTemp
upsEnvAmbientTemp.description: The reading of the ambient temperature in the vicinity of the UPS or SNMP agent.

upsEnvAmbientLowerLimit.name: upsEnvAmbientLowerLimit
upsEnvAmbientLowerLimit.description: The Lower Limit of the ambient temperature; if UpsEnvAmbientTemp falls below this value, the UpsAmbientTempBad alarm will occur.

upsEnvAmbientUpperLimit.name: upsEnvAmbientUpperLimit
upsEnvAmbientUpperLimit.description: The Upper Limit of the ambient temperature; if UpsEnvAmbientTemp rises above this value, the UpsAmbientTempBad alarm will occur. This value should be greater than UpsEnvAmbientLowerLimit.

upsEnvAmbientHumidity.name: upsEnvAmbientHumidity
upsEnvAmbientHumidity.description: The reading of the ambient humidity in the vicinity of the UPS or SNMP agent.

upsEnvRemoteTemp.name: upsEnvRemoteTemp
upsEnvRemoteTemp.description: The reading of a remote temperature sensor connected to the UPS or SNMP agent.

upsEnvRemoteHumidity.name: upsEnvRemoteHumidity
upsEnvRemoteHumidity.description: The reading of a remote humidity sensor connected to the UPS or SNMP agent.

upsEnvNumContacts.name: upsEnvNumContacts
upsEnvNumContacts.description: The number of Contacts in the UpsContactsTable. This object indicates the number of rows in the UpsContactsTable.

upsContactsTable.name: upsContactsTable
upsContactsTable.description: A list of Contact Sensing table entries. The number of entries is given by the value of UpsEnvNumContacts.

upsContactsTableEntry.name: upsContactsTableEntry
upsContactsTableEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular Contact input.

upsContactIndex.name: upsContactIndex
upsContactIndex.description: The Contact identifier; identical to the Contact Number.

upsContactType.name: upsContactType
upsContactType.description: The normal state for this contact. The 'other' state is the Active state for generating the UpstdContactActiveNotice trap. If anyChange(3) is selected, then this trap is sent any time the contact changes to either Open or Closed. No traps are sent if the Contact is set to notUsed(4). In many cases, the configuration for Contacts may be done by other means, so this object may be read-only.

upsContactState.name: upsContactState
upsContactState.description: The current state of the Contact input; the value is based on the open/closed input state and the setting for UpsContactType. When entering the openWithNotice(3) and closedWithNotice(4) states, no entries added to the UpsAlarmTable, but the UpstdContactActiveNotice trap is sent.

upsContactDescr.name: upsContactDescr
upsContactDescr.description: A label identifying the Contact. This object should be set by the administrator.

upsEnvRemoteTempLowerLimit.name: upsEnvRemoteTempLowerLimit
upsEnvRemoteTempLowerLimit.description: The Lower Limit of the remote temperature; if UpsEnvRemoteTemp falls below this value, the UpsRemoteTempBad alarm will occur.

upsEnvRemoteTempUpperLimit.name: upsEnvRemoteTempUpperLimit
upsEnvRemoteTempUpperLimit.description: The Upper Limit of the remote temperature; if UpsEnvRemoteTemp rises above this value, the UpsRemoteTempBad alarm will occur. This value should be greater than UpsEnvRemoteTempLowerLimit.

upsEnvRemoteHumidityLowerLimit.name: upsEnvRemoteHumidityLowerLimit
upsEnvRemoteHumidityLowerLimit.description: The Lower Limit of the remote humidity reading; if UpsEnvRemoteHumidity falls below this value, the UpsRemoteHumidityBad alarm will occur.

upsEnvRemoteHumidityUpperLimit.name: upsEnvRemoteHumidityUpperLimit
upsEnvRemoteHumidityUpperLimit.description: The Upper Limit of the remote humidity reading; if UpsEnvRemoteHumidity rises above this value, the UpsRemoteHumidityBad alarm will occur. This value should be greater than UpsEnvRemoteHumidityLowerLimit.

upsTestBattery.name: upsTestBattery
upsTestBattery.description: Setting this variable to startTest initiates the battery test. All other set values are invalid.

upsTestBatteryStatus.name: upsTestBatteryStatus
upsTestBatteryStatus.description: Reading this enumerated value gives an indication of the UPS Battery test status.

upsTestTrap.name: upsTestTrap
upsTestTrap.description: Setting this variable to startTestTrap initiates a TrapTest is sent out from HPMM. All other set values are invalid.

upsControlOutputOffDelay.name: upsControlOutputOffDelay
upsControlOutputOffDelay.description: Setting this value to other than zero will cause the UPS output to turn off after the number of seconds. Setting it to 0 will cause an attempt to abort a pending shutdown.

upsControlOutputOnDelay.name: upsControlOutputOnDelay
upsControlOutputOnDelay.description: Setting this value to other than zero will cause the UPS output to turn on after the number of seconds. Setting it to 0 will cause an attempt to abort a pending startup.

upsControlOutputOffTrapDelay.name: upsControlOutputOffTrapDelay
upsControlOutputOffTrapDelay.description: When UpsControlOutputOffDelay reaches this value, a trap will be sent.

upsControlOutputOnTrapDelay.name: upsControlOutputOnTrapDelay
upsControlOutputOnTrapDelay.description: When UpsControlOutputOnDelay reaches this value, a UpsOutputOff trap will be sent.

upsControlToBypassDelay.name: upsControlToBypassDelay
upsControlToBypassDelay.description: Setting this value to other than zero will cause the UPS output to go to Bypass after the number of seconds. If the Bypass is unavailable, this may cause the UPS to not supply power to the load. Setting it to 0 will cause an attempt to abort a pending shutdown.

upsLoadShedSecsWithRestart.name: upsLoadShedSecsWithRestart
upsLoadShedSecsWithRestart.description: Setting this value will cause the UPS output to turn off after the set number of seconds, then restart (after a UPS-defined 'down time') when the utility is again available. Unlike UpsControlOutputOffDelay, which might or might not, this object always maps to the XCP 0x8A Load Dump & Restart command, so the desired shutdown and restart behavior is guaranteed to happen. Once set, this command cannot be aborted. This is the preferred Control object to use when performing an On Battery OS Shutdown.

upsConfigOutputVoltage.name: upsConfigOutputVoltage
upsConfigOutputVoltage.description: The nominal UPS Output voltage per phase in volts.

upsConfigInputVoltage.name: upsConfigInputVoltage
upsConfigInputVoltage.description: The nominal UPS Input voltage per phase in volts.

upsConfigOutputWatts.name: upsConfigOutputWatts
upsConfigOutputWatts.description: The nominal UPS available real power output in watts.

upsConfigOutputFreq.name: upsConfigOutputFreq
upsConfigOutputFreq.description: The nominal output frequency in tenths of Hz.

upsConfigDateAndTime.name: upsConfigDateAndTime
upsConfigDateAndTime.description: Date and time information for the UPS. Setting this variable will initiate a set UPS date and time to this value. Reading this variable will return the UPS time and date. This value is not referenced to sysUpTime. It is simply the clock value from the UPS real time clock. Format is as follows: MM/DD/YYYY:HH:MM:SS.

upsConfigLowOutputVoltageLimit.name: upsConfigLowOutputVoltageLimit
upsConfigLowOutputVoltageLimit.description: The Lower limit for acceptable Output Voltage, per the UPS specifications.

upsConfigHighOutputVoltageLimit.name: upsConfigHighOutputVoltageLimit
upsConfigHighOutputVoltageLimit.description: The Upper limit for acceptable Output Voltage, per the UPS specifications.

upsNumReceptacles.name: upsNumReceptacles
upsNumReceptacles.description: The number of independently controllable Receptacles, as described in the UpsRecepTable.

upsRecepTable.name: upsRecepTable
upsRecepTable.description: The Aggregate Object with number of entries equal to NumReceptacles and including the UpsRecep group.

upsRecepIndex.name: upsRecepIndex
upsRecepIndex.description: The number of the Receptacle. Serves as index for Receptacle table.

upsRecepStatus.name: upsRecepStatus
upsRecepStatus.description: The Recep Status 1=On/Close, 2=Off/Open, 3=On w/Pending Off, 4=Off w/Pending ON, 5=Unknown.

upsRecepOffDelaySecs.name: upsRecepOffDelaySecs
upsRecepOffDelaySecs.description: The Delay until the Receptacle is turned Off. Setting this value to other than -1 will cause the UPS output to turn off after the number of seconds (0 is immediately). Setting it to -1 will cause an attempt to abort a pending shutdown. When this object is set while the UPS is On Battery, it is not necessary to set UpsRecepOnDelaySecs, since the outlet will turn back on automatically when power is available again.

upsRecepOnDelaySecs.name: upsRecepOnDelaySecs
upsRecepOnDelaySecs.description: The Delay until the Receptacle is turned On. Setting this value to other than -1 will cause the UPS output to turn on after the number of seconds (0 is immediately). Setting it to -1 will cause an attempt to abort a pending restart.

upsRecepAutoOffDelay.name: upsRecepAutoOffDelay
upsRecepAutoOffDelay.description: The delay after going On Battery until the Receptacle is automatically turned Off. A value of -1 means that this Output should never be turned Off automatically, but must be turned Off only by command. Values from 0 to 30 are valid, but probably innappropriate. The AutoOffDelay can be used to prioritize loads in the event of a prolonged power outage; less critical loads will turn off earlier to extend battery time for the more critical loads. If the utility power is restored before the AutoOff delay counts down to 0 on an outlet, that outlet will not turn Off.

upsRecepAutoOnDelay.name: upsRecepAutoOnDelay
upsRecepAutoOnDelay.description: Seconds delay after the Outlet is signaled to turn On before the Output is Automatically turned ON. A value of -1 means that this Output should never be turned On automatically, but only when specifically commanded to do so. A value of 0 means that the Receptacle should come On immediately at power-up or for an On command.

upsRecepShedSecsWithRestart.name: upsRecepShedSecsWithRestart
upsRecepShedSecsWithRestart.description: Setting this value will cause the UPS output to turn off after the set number of seconds, then restart (after a UPS-defined 'down time') when the utility is again available. Unlike UpsRecepOffDelaySecs, which might or might not, this object always maps to the XCP 0x8A Load Dump & Restart command, so the desired shutdown and restart behavior is guaranteed to happen. Once set, this command cannot be aborted.

upsTopologyType.name: upsTopologyType
upsTopologyType.description: Value which denotes the type of UPS by its power topology. Values are the same as those described in the XCP Topology block's Overall Topology field.

upsTopoMachineCode.name: upsTopoMachineCode
upsTopoMachineCode.description: ID Value which denotes the Compaq/HP model of the UPS for software. Values are the same as those described in the XCP Configuration block's Machine Code field.

upsTopoUnitNumber.name: upsTopoUnitNumber
upsTopoUnitNumber.description: Identifies which unit and what type of data is being reported. A value of 0 means that this MIB information comes from the top-level system view (eg, manifold module or system bypass cabinet reporting total system output). Standalone units also use a value of 0, since they are the 'full system' view. A value of 1 or higher indicates the number of the module in the system which is reporting only its own data in the HP MIB objects.

upsTopoPowerStrategy.name: upsTopoPowerStrategy
upsTopoPowerStrategy.description: Value which denotes which Power Strategy is currently set for the UPS. The values are: highAlert(1) - The UPS shall optimize its operating state to maximize its power-protection levels. This mode will be held for at most 24 hours. standard(2) - Balanced, normal power protection strategy. UPS will not enter HE operating mode from this setting. enableHighEfficiency(3) - The UPS is enabled to enter HE operating mode to optimize its operating state to maximize its efficiency, when conditions change to permit it (as determined by the UPS). forceHighEfficiency(4) - If this value is permitted to be Set for this UPS, and if conditions permit, requires the UPS to enter High Efficiency mode now, without delay (for as long as utility conditions permit). After successfully set to forceHighEfficiency(4), UpsTopoPowerStrategy changes to value enableHighEfficiency(3). UpsOutputSource will indicate if the UPS status is actually operating in High Efficiency mode.

pdrPanelLoadC.description: The percentage of load is the ratio of each output current to the rated output current to the panel.

pdrBreakerEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular output breaker of a particular panel.

pdrBreakerIndex.description: The index of breakers. 42 breakers in each panel, arranged in odd and even columns

pdrBreakerNumPosition.description: The position of this breaker in the panel, 1-phase breaker or n-m breaker for 2-phase or n-m-k breaker for 3-phase.

pdrBreakerNumPhases.name: pdrBreakerNumPhases
pdrBreakerNumPhases.description: The number of phase for this particular breaker.

pdrBreakerNumSequence.name: pdrBreakerNumSequence
pdrBreakerNumSequence.description: The sequence of this breaker. i.e. 1 for single phase 1,2 for 2-phase or 1,2,3 for 3-phase.

pdrBreakerRatedCurrent.name: pdrBreakerRatedCurrent
pdrBreakerRatedCurrent.description: The rated current in Amps for this particular breaker.

pdrBreakerMonthlyKWH.name: pdrBreakerMonthlyKWH
pdrBreakerMonthlyKWH.description: The accumulated KWH for this breaker since the beginning of this calendar month or since the last reset.

pdrBreakerYearlyKWH.name: pdrBreakerYearlyKWH
pdrBreakerYearlyKWH.description: The accumulated KWH for this breaker since the beginning of this calendar year or since the last reset.

pdrBreakerTotalKWH.name: pdrBreakerTotalKWH
pdrBreakerTotalKWH.description: The accumulated KWH for this breaker since it was put into service or since the last reset.

pdrBreakerCurrent.name: pdrBreakerCurrent
pdrBreakerCurrent.description: The measured output current for this breaker Current.

pdrBreakerCurrentPercent.name: pdrBreakerCurrentPercent
pdrBreakerCurrentPercent.description: The ratio of output current over rated current for each breaker.

pdrBreakerPercentWarning.description: The percentage of Warning set for this breaker.

pdrBreakerPercentOverload.name: pdrBreakerPercentOverload
